Saw this place on tv. Had to try it. In town for conference and needed a good start to the day. My wife and I ordered the original buttermilk waffle and two chicken tenders. It comes with powdered sugar and side of syrup. The waffles were perfectly cooked with a touch of crisp in the outside and soft and warm in the inside. A hint of vanilla topped off each bite. The tenders were tasty and hot and a perfect compliment to each bite. It was the perfect way to start the day

Ordered two  number 1s which is a buttermilk waffle and two chicken tenders. And a order of fries. Flavor was great! Waffle was tasty and chicken had the perfect another of seasoning. Strawberry kiwi drink was a bit too sweet and had a weird flavor to it. When we got our order and asked for more syrup we were looked at weird and cashier hesitated to give me extra. We got our bag and got to car we noticed we were short one platter which we paid for. When we returned to get it was asked “are u sure u didn’t get it” why the heck would I be asking if I did. That irritated me to no end. Would I go back probably not it was good but not that good to pay for parking and go through the hassle.

This was definitely the best chicken I've had in my life. Crispy outside, tender and juicy inside. My kids and I loved every bite. We got the wings and shrimp too. They were also fantastic. Loved the friendly staff and the beautiful Lexington Market too. All in all a great experience!

Crispy chicken, delicious waffles, sweet syrup and AMAZING staff.

Never ceases to amaze me. Sweet Mrs. Connie’s you can’t go wrong visiting her. The food has always been good since day 1. Service is outstanding. She knows all her customers by name. Check her out. We love you Mrs. Connie.

Stopped in while staying the night at the Lord Baltimore Hotel. Connie's new location is just a short walk from the lobby. We ordered the buttermilk waffle and 2 chicken tenders and it did not disappoint. The staff was friendly and prompt. Chicken was freshly battered and everything made to order. Meat was juicy and tender  and the waffles crisp but delicate. Good selection of condiments, although being a southern boy I only wish they offered gravy as an option. I have to travel to Baltimore often for chemo treatments at Johns Hopkins, and places like Connie's (and the Lord Baltimore) bring comfort to what would otherwise be an unpleasant trip  and have helped me to fall in love with the city of Baltimore.

Took my daughter to Lexington Market for the first time and she wanted to try chicken waffles for the first time, too.  I was skeptical.  The food took a bit longer than the other shops, but it definitely was worth it.  The chicken was moist and delicious, waffles light and fluffy.  We had a nice conversation with Ms. Connie herself while we waited.  My daughter is looking forward to returning.

Idk what the food taste like but i asked for a napkin because i just came in from the cold and my nose was running and was told no and then was told i can go and get one from the bathroom. That makes me not want to spend my money there. I'll probably never taste the food.

Connie deserves a chicken and waffle chain in her name. These are the best chicken and waffles money can buy. She was so sweet and kind to us. We definitely will be back. This is a must have stop in Baltimore.

I think I had the best waffle of my life here.  Better than Waffle House, better than others.  The waffles are warm, large and soft.  And flavored waffles have the full waffle batter flavored, not simply something tossed on top of a plain waffle, but toppings are available.  The chicken is moist with a crispy exterior.  Connie is doing something special here.  If you are concerned about the location, use UberEATS or their website to place a delivery order.  If you visit in person, there is a wait and you might have to wait behind some of those UberEATS orders.  Because this place is growing in popularity.  Connie needs to open up a full up restaurant.

Excellent. The waffles are light and fluffy but the real star is the chicken. The tenders were perfectly seasoned, perfectly breaded, and perfectly fried. Order about ten of them, you won't be disappointed.

In from out of town and felt right at home at Connie's. Chicken was light, crispy, and the perfect crunch for a thick maple syrup coated waffle. Ms. Connie was so nice and the half and half tea got us all the way back to our Inner Harbor hotel with a smile on our faces. Red Velvet waffle with powdered sugar is stand alone - no syrup needed. Will be back next year...maybe at the new location.
The service was great, she's friendly and sweet.  The food was good too. I had the cinnamon waffle and enjoyed every second of it.  I'll definitely be back.

Came here looking for groceries and decided to get chicken and waffles instead. Connie was very sweet and personable. I enjoyed my double stack chicken and chocolate chip waffles and will be coming back for more!
Best chicken & waffles in the city...and the staff is always polite & friendly make you feel at home I recommend this place to anyone that visits the city or just want some good food

I wanted to like this place but sorry to say food wasn't so good  Food was cold and chicken fried too hard. I'm all for supporting black owned businesses, they have great potential, however $12  plus tip is not worth cold food   and hard wings.

The cook stood upstairs talking to the security guard for 10 mins so by the time my family and I got our food and took it upstairs to eat. The lady (I think it was a lady) was yelling about the market closing in 8 mins but it was 5:10. Was unable to enjoy my food. Don't recommend visiting this place

I wanted to try for the first time.I'm always downtown and never stop there until the other day. Staff was very friendly.The food didn't wow me. I paid $12 for 2 waffles and 2 tenders which i think is a bit much when my tenders was very small so not much meat an they had a burnt taste.maybe because it was close to 5 o'clock Waffles was fine but 12 bucks an only 2 tenders that was burnt and small. Y'all should have 3 tenders with that or if they not a nice size add another one. I love to eat and support anyone. I don't think I'll go back unless they add more tenders an not burn them. Give me $12 worth i would spend it if it's worth the price.Good luck I'll keep an eye out to see if anything change.
Great food!!  Ms.  Connie and her sons are always pleasant.
The staff is courteous and professional. The chicken is crispy and moist and the waffles are flavorful. I highly recommend it to anybody looking for good food.
